Description: Porter Instrument Company is a leader in precision instruments for dental, medical and industrial applications.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Philadelphia Area, Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: PORTER Instrument Company is a global leader in analytical, dental, industrial and medical instrumentation. Since 1968, the company has specialized in the development, manufacture and sale of precision instruments that measure and control low flow gases and liquids for these applications. Our 54,000-sq. ft. fully integrated headquarters and manufacturing facility is located in Hatfield, PA, 35 miles northwest of Philadelphia. PORTER's passion for precision is a legacy dating from our founder's invention of a machine, using a heat/vacuum process, capable of precisely sizing the internal dimension and configuration of glass tubing within 50 millionths of an inch. This invention led to the first production of interchangeable, glass rotameter tubes. Today, in that same tradition of precision, PORTER flow and pressure control instruments, both standard and/or modified to customer design requirements, excel in some of the world's most performance critical applications. They play a vital role in the production of computer chips. They're trusted for the regulation and measurement of anesthetic gases in operating rooms world wide. They aid in the production of pharmaceutical drugs, cutting-edge biotech research, dental patient sedation and environmental monitoring. In short, when the application has no room for error, the world can put its trust in PORTER Instrument.

GET Parking, a self-parking solution, and GET Valet, an assisted parking solution, continuously adapt to customers’ changing needs by discovering insightful opportunities and operational efficiencies. Description: The HDBaseT Alliance was formed to promote and standardize HDBaseT technology for distribution of uncompressed HD multimedia.
Headquarters Regions: West Coast, Western US
Full Description: The HDBaseT Alliance was formed to promote and standardize HDBaseT technology for whole-home and commercial distribution of uncompressed HD multimedia. HDBaseT enables a single LAN cable to replace multiple cables and connectors in the home entertainment and business environment. It is optimized for video applications and it can connect all the entertainment devices in a setting by providing the 5Play convergence of uncompressed full HD digital video, audio, 100BaseT Ethernet, power over cable, and various control signals. The HDBaseT Alliance’s committees include HDBaseT Marketing Committee: a committee formed to help define, promote, and drive awareness of HDBaseT technology by highlighting its benefits and showing how it meets the needs of manufacturers, service and content providers, installers, and end consumers; HDBaseT Technical Committee: the committee responsible for the technical specification of HDBaseT and the related conformance tests suites; Certification Subcommittee: a committee focused on the development, implementation, and management of the Alliance Certification program; and Power over HdbaseT Subcommittee: a committee focused on the integration of power requirements into the HDBaseT specification. The HDBaseT Alliance was founded by [LG Electronics](https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/lg), [Samsung Electronics](https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/samsung-electronics), [Sony Pictures Entertainment](https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/sony-pictures-entertainment), and [Valens](https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/valens-semiconductor) in 2010 and is based in Beaverton, Oregon.

Description: UPGRADE INDUSTRIES is open source educational hardware that designs electronics adaptable for students, hobbyists, and professionals.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: We build stylish, open source, easy to use robotics hardware for students and hobbyists. Our main product line is BoardX. BoardX is a collection of electronic circuit boards that stack on top of one another to share resources, communicate, and extend the functionality of one another. This system is built on the motherboard that acts as both an electrical and structural foundation. Unlike similar products (but much like a familiar PC system), the motherboard does not come with a processor pre-installed. Processors come as simple, low cost add-on boards, which allows any processor - or multiple processors - to be used with the system. Current add-ons include non-volatile memory, Arduino compatible microcontroller, analog to digital converter, XBee mesh network radio, motor controller, do-it-yourself prototyping board and a PIC microprocessor board.
Industry Groups: Education, Hardware, Science and Engineering, Software
